latestPosts.caption:
Real confidence starts when you stop doing these 5 things!

	1.	Over-apologizing
Stop saying sorry for existing, for speaking up, for having boundaries. Confidence grows when you stop shrinking yourself to make others comfortable.

	2.	Seeking validation for every little thing
If you keep asking, “Is this okay?” “Do I look fine?” you’re telling your mind you don’t trust yourself. Start making choices that you love. That’s the kind of energy that attracts.

	3.	Comparing yourself constantly
You’re not late. You’re not behind. You’re on your path. The more you focus on someone else’s timeline, the more you delay your own growth.

	4.	Waiting to feel ‘ready’
Confidence doesn’t come from perfection, it comes from taking action even when you’re unsure. Show up scared. You’ll get stronger every time.

	5.	Speaking negatively about yourself
Your words shape your reality. Every time you say “I’m not good enough,” your mind listens. Flip the script. Talk to yourself with the same love and hype you give others.
